<sect2 id="md__c_1_2_users_2_arie_2_develop_2hb__215_2_backend_2_readme_1autotoc_md1">
<title>Functionalities</title>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Utilizes graphql to have a single endpoint where requests are mapped</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Allows users to edit profile information and create posts</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Users can join or leave posts and make comments</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="md__c_1_2_users_2_arie_2_develop_2hb__215_2_backend_2_readme_1autotoc_md2">
<title>Pre requisites</title>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Maven has to be installed on command line OR your IDE must be configured with maven</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Java version 17 or higher</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="md__c_1_2_users_2_arie_2_develop_2hb__215_2_backend_2_readme_1autotoc_md3">
<title>To Run the project</title>
<para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Command Line (Make sure that you are in the folder containing pom.xml) <computeroutput> mvn clean install</computeroutput> <computeroutput>cd target</computeroutput> <computeroutput>java -jar sportsphere-1.0.0.jar</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>IDE : Right click on <ref refid="_application_8java" kindref="compound">Application.java</ref> and run as Java Application </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
